<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4524] ReturnFields could not support hash &apos;#&apos; in filed name </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4524</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If some fields start with &apos;#&apos; and we try to put it in fl param, this field and all next fields are not in response document&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With query:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  q=&lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;amp;fl=score,#id,myOtherField&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Document response is like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   SolrDocument&lt;/p&gt;
{score=3.809621}

&lt;p&gt;this bug is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2719&quot; title=&quot;REGRESSION ReturnFields incorrect parse fields with hyphen - breaks existing &amp;quot;fl=my-field-name&amp;quot; type usecases&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-2719&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2719&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4374&quot; title=&quot;Solr could not support numeric field name in return&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4374&quot;&gt;SOLR-4374&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
