                            <comment id="13593559" author="bpoussin" created="Tue, 5 Mar 2013 16:40:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your unit test, and your hypothesis with # and URL can be right, but i used solrj and i don&apos;t write myself url &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. Perhaps there is bug in solrj about &apos;#&apos; encoding ?&lt;br/&gt;
